{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":554,"text":"It's wonderful to be here"},{"time":2785,"text":"to talk about my journey,"},{"time":4871,"text":"to talk about the wheelchair"},{"time":6605,"text":"and the freedom it has bought me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9245,"text":"I started using a wheelchair 16 years ago"},{"time":11882,"text":"when an extended illness"},{"time":14016,"text":"changed the way I could access the world."},{"time":17602,"text":"When I started using the wheelchair,"},{"time":19979,"text":"it was a tremendous new freedom."},{"time":22564,"text":"I'd seen my life slip away and become restricted."},{"time":25650,"text":"It was like having an enormous new toy."},{"time":28220,"text":"I could whiz around and feel the wind in my face again."},{"time":32250,"text":"Just being out on the street was exhilarating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35758,"text":"But even though I had this newfound joy and freedom,"},{"time":40160,"text":"people's reaction completely changed towards me."},{"time":43712,"text":"It was as if they couldn't see me anymore,"},{"time":46192,"text":"as if an invisibility cloak had descended."},{"time":50191,"text":"They seemed to see me in terms of their assumptions"},{"time":53412,"text":"of what it must be like to be in a wheelchair."},{"time":57640,"text":"When I asked people their associations with the wheelchair,"},{"time":62552,"text":"they used words like \"limitation,\" \"fear,\""},{"time":66106,"text":"\"pity\" and \"restriction.\""},{"time":69131,"text":"I realized I'd internalized these responses"},{"time":73900,"text":"and it had changed who I was on a core level."},{"time":77437,"text":"A part of me had become alienated from myself."},{"time":81627,"text":"I was seeing myself not from my perspective,"},{"time":85212,"text":"but vividly and continuously from the perspective"},{"time":89374,"text":"of other people's responses to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92271,"text":"As a result, I knew I needed to make my own stories"},{"time":97396,"text":"about this experience,"},{"time":99635,"text":"new narratives to reclaim my identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102411,"text":"[\"Finding Freedom: 'By creating our own stories we learn to take the texts of our lives as seriously as we do 'official' narratives.' â€” Davis 2009, TEDx Women\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105515,"text":"I started making work"},{"time":107593,"text":"that aimed to communicate something"},{"time":110409,"text":"of the joy and freedom I felt when using a wheelchair --"},{"time":115527,"text":"a power chair -- to negotiate the world."},{"time":120141,"text":"I was working to transform these internalized responses,"},{"time":126726,"text":"to transform the preconceptions that had so shaped"},{"time":130521,"text":"my identity when I started using a wheelchair,"},{"time":133702,"text":"by creating unexpected images."},{"time":137466,"text":"The wheelchair became an object to paint and play with."},{"time":143687,"text":"When I literally started leaving"},{"time":145728,"text":"traces of my joy and freedom,"},{"time":149294,"text":"it was exciting to see"},{"time":151242,"text":"the interested and surprised responses from people."},{"time":155744,"text":"It seemed to open up new perspectives,"},{"time":158633,"text":"and therein lay the paradigm shift."},{"time":161528,"text":"It showed that an arts practice"},{"time":163602,"text":"can remake one's identity"},{"time":165945,"text":"and transform preconceptions by revisioning the familiar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170729,"text":"So when I began to dive, in 2005,"},{"time":174642,"text":"I realized scuba gear extends your range of activity"},{"time":178168,"text":"in just the same way as a wheelchair does,"},{"time":180827,"text":"but the associations attached to scuba gear"},{"time":183419,"text":"are ones of excitement and adventure,"},{"time":186019,"text":"completely different to people's responses to the wheelchair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189843,"text":"So I thought, \"I wonder what'll happen"},{"time":192987,"text":"if I put the two together?\" (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":197299,"text":"And the underwater wheelchair that has resulted"},{"time":201491,"text":"has taken me on the most amazing journey"},{"time":204198,"text":"over the last seven years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206467,"text":"So to give you an idea of what that's like,"},{"time":209955,"text":"I'd like to share with you one of the outcomes"},{"time":212841,"text":"from creating this spectacle,"},{"time":214937,"text":"and show you what an amazing journey it's taken me on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218738,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":428435,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":435236,"text":"It is the most amazing experience,"},{"time":438215,"text":"beyond most other things I've experienced in life."},{"time":441856,"text":"I literally have the freedom to move"},{"time":444953,"text":"in 360 degrees of space"},{"time":447592,"text":"and an ecstatic experience of joy and freedom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451352,"text":"And the incredibly unexpected thing"},{"time":453969,"text":"is that other people seem to see and feel that too."},{"time":458159,"text":"Their eyes literally light up,"},{"time":460537,"text":"and they say things like, \"I want one of those,\""},{"time":463791,"text":"or, \"If you can do that, I can do anything.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":467473,"text":"And I'm thinking, it's because in that moment"},{"time":471095,"text":"of them seeing an object"},{"time":473648,"text":"they have no frame of reference for,"},{"time":475559,"text":"or so transcends the frames of reference"},{"time":478359,"text":"they have with the wheelchair,"},{"time":480104,"text":"they have to think in a completely new way."},{"time":483136,"text":"And I think that moment of completely new thought"},{"time":487480,"text":"perhaps creates a freedom"},{"time":489978,"text":"that spreads to the rest of other people's lives."},{"time":494004,"text":"For me, this means that they're seeing"},{"time":497196,"text":"the value of difference,"},{"time":499546,"text":"the joy it brings"},{"time":501466,"text":"when instead of focusing on loss or limitation,"},{"time":505286,"text":"we see and discover the power and joy"},{"time":509690,"text":"of seeing the world from exciting new perspectives."},{"time":514097,"text":"For me, the wheelchair becomes"},{"time":515796,"text":"a vehicle for transformation."},{"time":518141,"text":"In fact, I now call the underwater wheelchair \"Portal,\""},{"time":521921,"text":"because it's literally pushed me through"},{"time":524125,"text":"into a new way of being,"},{"time":526003,"text":"into new dimensions and into a new level of consciousness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529737,"text":"And the other thing is,"},{"time":531282,"text":"that because nobody's seen or heard"},{"time":533754,"text":"of an underwater wheelchair before,"},{"time":536249,"text":"and creating this spectacle is about creating"},{"time":539092,"text":"new ways of seeing, being and knowing,"},{"time":541929,"text":"now you have this concept in your mind."},{"time":544877,"text":"You're all part of the artwork too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548676,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}